Analyze all files in this folder mvpEgas/prereq/ before implement any feature 

Project Setup & Folder Structure to strictly follow
Folder Structure:
src/
├── pages/
│   ├── auth/             # Login/Register pages
│   ├── dashboard/        # Dashboard pages
│   ├── catalog/          # Product catalog pages
│   ├── reports/          # Reports pages
│   ├── orders/           # Order details pages
│   └── common/           # Shared page components
├── components/
│   ├── auth/             # Auth components (e.g., LoginForm)
│   ├── dashboard/        # Dashboard widgets (e.g., charts)
│   ├── catalog/          # Catalog components (e.g., ProductCard)
│   ├── reports/          # Report components (e.g., OrderTable)
│   └── common/           # Reusable components (e.g., Button, Input)
├── utils/                # Utility functions (e.g., API calls, helpers)
├── lib/                  # Supabase client setup
├── styles/               # Global CSS/Tailwind styles
└── app/                  # Next.js App Router (if using App Router)

2. Feature Development Order
#	Feature	Description	Order
1	Authentication	User login/register with Supabase Auth.	1st
2	Dashboard	Core metrics (GMV, orders, returns) with charts.	2nd
3	Product Catalog	Base/Master/Marketplace catalog CRUD with image upload.	3rd
4	SKU Calculator	Cost calculation tool (break-even price, profit margin).	4th
5	Reports	Order/Return/Reconciliation reports with filters.	5th
6	Order Details	View individual order details (shipping, returns, payments).	6th
7	Multi-Tenancy	Tenant isolation using Supabase row-level security (RLS).	7th
8	ETL Pipeline	Data ingestion from Amazon SPI-API to Supabase.	8th
9	Image Processing	AI-powered background removal (Cloudinary/Supabase Integration).	9th
10	Deployment	Vercel/AWS deployment with Supabase environment variables.	10th



-----------------------------------

firebase is the database that is being used
Create all necessary firebase collections
